This paper discusses the development of QoS-aware service-oriented architectures, which falls under the sub-category of computer science focused on service-oriented computing and software engineering. Specifically, the paper discusses approaches for web service description and discovery, which involves topics such as semantic web, web services, and distributed systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (social and information networks), cs.DL (digital libraries), cs.SE (software engineering), cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing), and cs.CE (computational engineering, finance, and science).
